	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=/db/poster.html?user=228225><span id= >Emanonion</span></a><br><span id=notbold>17 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I dont know how many times you have killed Avatar of Dust for the Rune Stamped Blade, but it isnt an event ring that you really want to do a lot. As a matter of fact most guilds do it just enough times to get a couple of people the piece they need for the Xegony island key, which if you dont know is like 1-2 kills because it usually drops more than 1. So if you have more than 1 bard that wants it they are probably SOL and even with the couple of kills you might do you may not see this drop. So the Rhythm of Xegony starts looking better and better all the time to bards that dont already have something of equal or better quality.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=762403 target=akztarg> Emanonion </a></td></tr>
